---
// HowItWorks.astro - A visual explanation of how Bomfather works
---

<section class="py-16 bg-white">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold font-heading mb-4">How Bomfather Works</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-mid-gray max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Bomfather uses eBPF technology to monitor kernel-level activities in AI systems, creating R-AIBOMs with tamper-evident audit trails while actively blocking malicious accesses.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="relative">
      <!-- Connected steps with flow lines -->
      <div class="hidden md:block absolute left-0 right-0 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 h-1 bg-light-gray z-0"></div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 relative z-10">
        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="bg-light-gray p-6 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4 text-xl font-bold">
            1
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Trust Definition</h3>
          <p class="text-mid-gray">
            Users define which files and resources are trusted in their AI workflows.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="bg-light-gray p-6 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4 text-xl font-bold">
            2
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Kernel Monitoring</h3>
          <p class="text-mid-gray">
            Bomfather attaches eBPF probes to monitor system calls during AI training and inference.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="bg-light-gray p-6 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4 text-xl font-bold">
            3
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Threat Detection & Prevention</h3>
          <p class="text-mid-gray">
            Identifies and blocks unauthorized accesses in real-time using the trust model while allowing legitimate operations.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Step 4 -->
        <div class="bg-light-gray p-6 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg text-center">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4 text-xl font-bold">
            4
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">R-AIBOM Creation</h3>
          <p class="text-mid-gray">
            Creates cryptographically verified Runtime AI Bills of Materials documenting the system's activities and security events.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="mt-12 text-center">
      <p class="mb-6 text-mid-gray">
        The result is both a secure runtime environment and a comprehensive Runtime AI Bill of Materials (R-AIBOM) with cryptographic evidence of all legitimate activities and blocked threats.
